## API Contract

### Endpoint

```
POST /api/rpg/adventure/simulation/action
Content-Type: application/json

Request Body:
{
    "setup": { /* full adventure setup object */ },
    "action": {
        "type": "intervene_thread" | "support_faction" | "escalate_conflict",
        "target_id": "thread_id_or_faction_id"
    }
}

Response (200 OK):
{
    "success": true,
    "updated_setup": { /* updated setup with new simulation_state */ },
    "simulation_state": { /* after_state with tick advanced */ },
    "simulation_diff": { /* structured diff */ },
    "summary": ["1 thread de-escalated", ...],
    "scenes": [{ /* generated scenes */ }],
    "graph": { /* world graph */ },
    "simulation": { /* simulation summary */ },
    "inspector": { /* entity inspector */ }
}
```

### Frontend Integration

The frontend dispatches actions via:
```js
_handleSceneAction(actionType, scene) {
    const actionMap = {
        'intervene': 'intervene_thread',
        'support': 'support_faction',
        'escalate': 'escalate_conflict'
    };
    
    fetch('/api/rpg/adventure/simulation/action', {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: {'Content-Type': 'application/json'},
        body: JSON.stringify({
            setup: _getCurrentSetup(),
            action: {
                type: actionMap[actionType],
                target_id: scene.actors[0]
            }
        })
    })
    .then(r => r.json())
    .then(res => {
        wi.simulationRuntime.state = res.simulation_state;
        wi.simulationRuntime.lastDiff = res.simulation_diff;
        _renderStep();
    });
}
```

